dep_iconv is detected in meson.build but was never added to the executable's
dependencies list, causing iconv symbols to be unresolved at link time. The
workaround was a xclock.confopt setting -Dc_link_args='-liconv', but that
causes meson to replace (rather than augment) the LDFLAGS-derived link args,
dropping the sanitizer rpath /opt/X11/lib/sanitizers.

Fix by adding dep_iconv to the executable's dependencies so meson handles
iconv linking through its own mechanism, preserving LDFLAGS as expected.

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
index 6b4754d..809babb 100644
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -124,7 +124,7 @@ add_project_arguments('-D_CONST_X_STRING', language: ['c'])
 executable(
   'xclock',
   [config_h, 'Clock.c', 'Clock.h', 'ClockP.h', 'xclock.c'],
-  dependencies: [deps, extra_deps],
+  dependencies: [deps, extra_deps, dep_iconv],
   install: true
 )
